fields.text: He's such a sleepy little bundle. I could watch him sleep all day.
Conifer is starting to smile more and is really becoming active! He kicks and kicks when he's excited.
Conifer discovered his reflection in my sunglasses today. It's so fun watching him develop.
Conifer loves the sweet little rattle given to him by John and Sally Mae. He tries to stuff the whole thing in his mouth, which is hilarious to watch.
We've been hanging out outside a lot. Conifer loves to play in the pool. He's laughing a lot lately.
Conifer loves blueberries! Really, any fruit. And he's such a messy little eater, but so fun to watch.

Conifer loves all of his Denver friends. He's met Evette, Jason, Lauren, and Nick. Today we went on a seven-mile hike with Nick! Conifer loved hanging out near the alpine lake, and slept all the way home.
While riding in the back of the car today, Conifer reached out, grabbed the whole apple I was eating and took a big bite out of it! Ha! It's amazing what you can do with only two teeth.
Now that he has teeth, we've introduced tooth brushing to the nighttime routine. He seems to really love it, but it's probably the pear-flavored toothpaste.
I love playing my horn for Conifer and watching how he responds to the music.
Conifer loves bathtime! It's one of my favorite parts of the day. He thinks it's so funny to splash us.
